author: Times-News
title: Prep Roundup: Rockingham County girls win league title in golf
text: Posted Oct. 13, 2015 at 12:18 AM Updated at 12:24 AM Posted Oct. 13, 2015 at 12:18 AM Updated at 12:24 AM GREENSBORO — Olivia John of RockinghamCounty fired a 1-over par 73 and teammate Hailey Joy was one stroke behind at 74 leading the Cougars to the Mid-State 3-A Conference Tournament team title in girls’ golf Monday at Greensboro National Golf Club. WilliamsHigh School placed second at 272 followed by Northern Guilford (273), Western Alamance (293), EasternAlamance (316), EdenMorehead (318), McMichael (339) and Eastern Guilford (343). Kendall Dobbins of Northern Guilford finished third at 6-over 78. Kayla Smith (79) and Katherine Cox (82) of Williams placed fourth and fifth respectively. Emma Roberts (86) of Western Alamance and Autumn Bryant (89) of Eastern Alamance followed the Willams pair in sixth and seventh place. Girls’ tennis Abby Farlow of Western Alamance defeated RockinghamCounty’s Ally Gagnon 9-8 (3) in an elimination match of the Mid-State 3-A Conference qualifier tournament at Burlington Tennis Center to advance into the state playoffs. Farlow had an earlier first round victory against Rachel Fallin of McMichael 6-0, 6-3 but fell to Eden Morehead’s Scotlyn McDowell 7-6 (8), 6-2 in the second round. Carter Jeurgens and Emma Wright of Northern Guilford, Hailey Rizza of Rockingham County, Jamie Cruise of McMichael and Alexus Brown of Eden Morehead join Farlow and McDowell as qualifiers for the conference. Boys’ soccer WilliamsHigh School converted on five shootout goals as the Bulldogs defeated visiting EdenMorehead in the penalty-kick shootout after playing to a 1-1 tie in a Mid-State 3-A Conference game. The shootout tally was 5-3. Earlier, George Ellington scored off an assist from Miguel Martinez for the Bulldogs (7-6-1 overall, 4-2-0 Mid-State 3-A). ■ THE BURLINGTON SCHOOL 2, SALEM BAPTIST CHRISTIAN SCHOOL 1: At Winston-Salem, Jo Jeffers scored the game-winning goal on a rebounded shot and The Burlington School picked up its second Triad Athletic Conference victory. Caleb Pickett scored early in the second half for the Spartans (2-8, 7-10). Volleyball Eden Morehead roared back from two sets down to defeat host WilliamsHigh School 21-25, 15-25, 25-18, 26-24, 15-10 in a Mid-State 3-A Conference match. Rebecca Hunnicutt (13 digs, 12 kills, two blocks), Dinaisya Harrison (10 kills, 10 digs), Kenzie Vance (22 digs, three aces), Bella Huerta (30 assists, eight digs, three kills) and Mekayla White (12 kills) paced the Bulldogs (9-11, 5-9). Eden Morehead is 14-3, 11-3. By Times-News
